[1]
Date: Wed, 1 Oct 2003 8:10:28 AM
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: KOB-TV, Albuquerque / AP 1 Oct 2003 [edited]
<http://www.kobtv.com/index.cfm?viewer=storyviewer&id=5023&cat=BUSINESS>

Old Santa Fe Trail, Route 66 food products recalled
----------------------------------------------------
Beef jerky sold under the name "Old Santa Fe Trail" or "Route 66" is being
recalled after 19 of 21 people confirmed to have salmonellosis -- a
bacterial infection -- reported eating the jerky. That report was issued
Tue, 30 Sep 2003 by the Albuquerque municipal Environmental Health Department.
It says salmonella contamination was found in the jerky, and the
Albuquerque plant that makes the beef jerky has been closed. The jerky --
spiced with New Mexico chiles -- was marketed statewide in grocery stores,
convenience stores, the state fair, and by mail order.
