Date: Tue, 30 Sep 2003 16:44:52 -0500
From: Harry Hull <Harry.Hull@state.mn.us>

2 previous New Mexico outbreaks of salmonellosis related to beef jerky are
found in the following MMWRs. (Carne seca translates as dried beef, i.e.,
beef jerky)
Outbreak of Salmonellosis associated with beef jerky -- New Mexico, 1995.
MMWR Morb Mortal Wkly Rep. 1995;44:785-8.
Salmonellosis Associated with Carne Seca -- New Mexico MMWR Morb Mortal
Wkly Rep. 1985;34:645.
--
Harry F. Hull, M.D.
